Vulnerability Scan

    Start the dashboard.

    Click Start New Vulnerability Scan.

    Enter a test target like http://testphp.vulnweb.com.

    Watch real‑time progress and view the report when complete.

Brute‑Force Scan

    Click Start New Brute‑Force Scan.

    Enter a login URL (e.g., http://testphp.vulnweb.com/login.php).

    The scanner will try the wordlist combinations and report any valid credentials.

Using Kali Wordlists
bash

export BRUTE_USERLIST=/usr/share/wordlists/seclists/Usernames/top-usernames-shortlist.txt
export BRUTE_PASSLIST=/usr/share/wordlists/seclists/Passwords/Common-Credentials/10k-most-common.txt
python dashboard.py

🧪 Testing with a Vulnerable Site

    Use DVWA (Damn Vulnerable Web Application) or WebGoat locally.

    Never scan sites you don’t own.
